==English==
===Etymology===
Afrikaans diminutive of ''stomp'': a stump.
===Noun===
'''Stompie'''
#(South African) A cigarette butt.
#* 11.01.73 Eastrern Province Hearald: “be careful with lighted cigarettes, matches stompies …becaust they can start fires.
===Derived terms===
*picking up stompies: picking up rumours from the tail end of a conversation.
===Reference===
1978: A Dictionary of South African English: Editor Jean Branford: Oxford.
